<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="107" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="107">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="107">
All diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microperus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microperus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Microperus</taxonomicName>
present: small size, elytral punctures aligned in striae, and prolonged body shape (
<bibRefCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="107">Hulcr and Cognato in press</bibRefCitation>
). Similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microperus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microperus pometianus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pometianus">Microperus pometianus</taxonomicName>
, but slightly longer, with distinctly elevated and long declivital costa.
</paragraph>
